        <b><span id="titleLabel">1.1 - What's Next: Coming face-to-face with designers shaping the future of games.</span></b>
        <table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <tr>
                <td class="tableCell" colspan="2"><span id="dateTimeLabel">Wednesday, May 10, 9:30 AM - 11:00 AM</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="tableCell" colspan="2"><span id="roomLabel">Room 404AB</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="tableCell" colspan="2"><span id="descriptionLabel">The ongoing conversation about the best use of Hollywood licenses or the importance of a game's soundtrack may qualify as today's big-buzz topics, but addressing the opportunities and challenges facing today's game industry is only half the story. What about upcoming games that go beyond today's trends and prosaic preoccupations? What's next? What's <i> really</i> next? This session will invite designers who have already made an impact on game design today to share their personal vision of tomorrow's game experience and what they are doing to shape it. What new concepts are they working with? What's their idea of perfect gameplay? What should tomorrow's games aspire to? And what chances need to be taken to get there?</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td id="panelistLable" width="18%" class="tableCell">Moderator / Panelist</td>

                <td class="tableCell"><span id="moderatorLabel">David Perry, Executive Video Game Industry Consultant - GameConsultants.com</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="tableCell">Panelists:</td>
                <td class="tableCell"><span id="panelistsLabel">Todd Howard, Executive Producer - Bethesda Game Studios<BR>Ken Levine, President and Co-founder - Irrational Games<BR>51 Suda, CEO, Game Designer, Director, Scenario Writer - grasshopper manufacture<BR>Tim Willits, Co-Owner and Lead Designer of Doom 3 - id Software, Inc.<BR></span></td>
